# Pin the packet-analysis seccomp profiles to LF line endings (ADR-0031 §3 /
# ADR-0049 blocker 3). These JSON profiles are compared as RAW BYTES by the
# lockstep CI gate (.github/workflows/ci.yml job `infra`) against their
# deploy/kubernetes/netops/seccomp and in-package backend/app/engines/packet
# copies (all pinned eol=lf there). Under core.autocrlf=true a Windows clone
# would materialize CRLF in the working tree and the byte-for-byte `cmp` would
# FALSE-RED on pure line-ending churn. Pinning eol=lf keeps every copy LF
# regardless of the cloner's autocrlf setting, so the gate compares CONTENT.
seccomp/*.json text eol=lf
